I. Background 


The proposed rule is a revision of existing regulations codified at 31 CFR part 344, published on July 7, 1989, at 54
FR 28752, with technical corrections published July 7, 1993, at 58 FR 31908. 
In 1992, the Bureau of the Public Debt established the Division of Special Investments at its offices in Parkersburg,
West Virginia (WV). The primary mission of the Division of Special Investments has been to provide policy guidance
and direction for the State and Local Government Series securities program. The Division has reviewed the current
processing environment and is implementing operational and regulatory changes which are expected to benefit investors
in United States Treasury securities of the State and Local Government Series by providing streamlined procedures,
a centralized processing facility, and improved customer services. 




