If this approach were to be adopted, the Commission welcomes comments on who should be covered by the new provision,
and during what timeframe it should apply. Should this be limited to expenses incurred by the candidate, or the candidate
and his or her immediate family, or should it also include campaign staff? If the latter, should such staff be limited,
either by number or position held in the campaign? The Commission notes that, where a number of candidates sought the
nomination, the expenses of these candidates, their families, and accompanying campaign staff could be substantial.

