Likewise, CPSC reports that, based upon data from its 
National Electronic Injury Surveillance System (NEISS) (NEISS is 
a probability sample of hospital emergency rooms in the United 
States that is used by the CPSC to measure the magnitude of the 
injury problem associated with consumer products and to provide a 
source for followup investigations of selected cases), there was 
a significant upward trend in the estimated number of hospital 
