2. CPSC Case Reports 


CPSC considers iron-containing products to be potentially 
hazardous to children and, thus, has taken a number of 
significant steps designed to reduce the risk from these 
products. As part of its efforts, CPSC has collected detailed 
information on pediatric iron poisoning fatalities and has also 
conducted followup (from NEISS data) investigations of incidents 
of nonfatal pediatric iron ingestion where the victim was taken 
to a hospital emergency room. In order to evaluate the available 
data on specific occurrences of iron poisoning as fully as 
possible, FDA obtained from CPSC the case reports on 37 fatal 
